                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/1424: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bliss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-10-11T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >October 11, 1931—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 4:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>109. Your 69, October 9, 6 p.m. Minister for Foreign Affairs said yesterday that
                    he will be glad to recommend informally that Bolivian Government be represented
                    at November 11 conference; also that troops of both parties to Chaco dispute
                    remain within their respective limits.</p>
                <p>He does not consider that either side means war but notes reciprocal tendency to
                    take advantage of present abnormal situation to endeavor to score points against
                    opponents. During next few days Doctor Bioy intends to see if any further
                    negotiations are possible with a view to renewal of Paraguayan-Bolivian
                    diplomatic relations. These were previously conducted by Doctor Bosch in person
                    but have of late been in abeyance by reason of above-mentioned tendency.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bliss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
